{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-detail-js","path":"/post/how-to-implement-magnifier-widget-in-magento-2/","result":{"data":{"wpPost":{"title":"How to Implement Magnifier Widget in Magento 2","content":"\n<p>Magento 2 is a widely-used e-commerce platform offering a powerful set of features and tools for managing online stores. These features include marketing automation, customer management, inventory management, and order tracking.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>A key feature that enhances the user experience is the <a href=\"https://developer.adobe.com/commerce/frontend-core/javascript/jquery-widgets/magnifier/#:~:text=Magnifier%20is%20a%20widget%20that,in%20your%20local%20theme%20view.\" class=\"ek-link\">magnifier widget</a>, allowing customers to zoom in on product images for a closer and more detailed view. This feature is especially useful for products with intricate details or small print.Â </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Implementing the magnifier widget in Magento 2 is an easy process involving basic configuration and customization. This blog will guide you through the necessary steps for <strong><em>how to implement a magnifier widget in the Magento 2</em></strong> store. We will provide tips and best practices for optimizing the widget to ensure a seamless and engaging user experience for your customers, from selecting the right widget extension to installation and configuration on your site.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Steps to Implement Magnifier Widget in Magento 2</h2>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Step 1: Create a New Theme</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The first step in implementing a magnifier widget is to create a new theme. This can be done in the following steps:</p>\n\n\n\n<p>1. Log in to your Magento 2 admin panel.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>2. Go to Content &gt; Design &gt; Configuration.</p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><div data-gatsby-image-wrapper=\"\" style=\"position:relative;overflow:hidden;display:inline-block;vertical-align:top\" class=\"gatsby-image-wrapper gatsby-image-wrapper-constrained wp-image-1811 inline-gatsby-image-wrapper\"><div style=\"max-width:529px;display:block\"><img alt=\"\" role=\"presentation\" aria-hidden=\"true\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg%20height=&#x27;559&#x27;%20width=&#x27;529&#x27;%20xmlns=&#x27;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#x27;%20version=&#x27;1.1&#x27;%3E%3C/svg%3E\" style=\"max-width:100%;display:block;position:static\"/></div><div aria-hidden=\"true\" data-placeholder-image=\"\" style=\"height:100%;left:0;position:absolute;top:0;width:100%\"></div><img data-gatsby-image-ssr=\"\" data-wp-inline-image=\"1\" data-main-image=\"\" style=\"height:100%;left:0;position:absolute;top:0;transform:translateZ(0);transition:opacity 250ms linear;width:100%;will-change:opacity;opacity:0\" sizes=\"(min-width: 529px) 529px, 100vw\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" data-src=\"/_gatsby/image/27276ed37ae8f6c4e301cee9153d4e86/9ccdb62261059fcb57590f68259af6a6/image-9.png?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwebguru.dev%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F04%2Fimage-9.png&amp;a=w%3D132%26h%3D139%26fm%3Dpng%26q%3D90&amp;cd=2023-04-13T03%3A55%3A54\" data-srcset=\"/_gatsby/image/27276ed37ae8f6c4e301cee9153d4e86/9ccdb62261059fcb57590f68259af6a6/image-9.png?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwebguru.dev%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F04%2Fimage-9.png&amp;a=w%3D132%26h%3D139%26fm%3Dpng%26q%3D90&amp;cd=2023-04-13T03%3A55%3A54 132w,/_gatsby/image/27276ed37ae8f6c4e301cee9153d4e86/f881143edba5828131d9d56b02a6bcfd/image-9.png?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwebguru.dev%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F04%2Fimage-9.png&amp;a=w%3D265%26h%3D280%26fm%3Dpng%26q%3D90&amp;cd=2023-04-13T03%3A55%3A54 265w,/_gatsby/image/27276ed37ae8f6c4e301cee9153d4e86/3ac25ae87143c83502112b005580e714/image-9.png?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwebguru.dev%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F04%2Fimage-9.png&amp;a=w%3D529%26h%3D559%26fm%3Dpng%26q%3D90&amp;cd=2023-04-13T03%3A55%3A54 529w\" alt=\"Steps to Implement Magnifier Widget in Ma