ty:0\" sizes=\"(min-width: 1024px) 1024px, 100vw\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"/_gatsby/image/79a6a10d0413605c35bcb6d9ebf9e3e6/3fd703fd789c940ed30c9c507ff9d5dc/image-10.png?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwebguru.dev%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F04%2Fimage-10.png&amp;a=w%3D256%26h%3D42%26fm%3Dpng%26q%3D90&amp;cd=2023-04-13T03%3A57%3A54\" srcSet=\"/_gatsby/image/79a6a10d0413605c35bcb6d9ebf9e3e6/3fd703fd789c940ed30c9c507ff9d5dc/image-10.png?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwebguru.dev%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F04%2Fimage-10.png&amp;a=w%3D256%26h%3D42%26fm%3Dpng%26q%3D90&amp;cd=2023-04-13T03%3A57%3A54 256w,/_gatsby/image/79a6a10d0413605c35bcb6d9ebf9e3e6/8b90fea6c5b5e215f87d6b6653e835f0/image-10.png?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwebguru.dev%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F04%2Fimage-10.png&amp;a=w%3D512%26h%3D85%26fm%3Dpng%26q%3D90&amp;cd=2023-04-13T03%3A57%3A54 512w,/_gatsby/image/79a6a10d0413605c35bcb6d9ebf9e3e6/5663903fab88f184af92ef37a377bd4c/image-10.png?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwebguru.dev%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F04%2Fimage-10.png&amp;a=w%3D1024%26h%3D170%26fm%3Dpng%26q%3D90&amp;cd=2023-04-13T03%3A57%3A54 1024w\" alt=\"Steps to Implement Magnifier Widget in Magento 2 2\"/></noscript><script type=\"module\">const t=\"undefined\"!=typeof HTMLImageElement&&\"loading\"in HTMLImageElement.prototype;if(t){const t=document.querySelectorAll(\"img[data-main-image]\");for(let e of t){e.dataset.src&&(e.setAttribute(\"src\",e.dataset.src),e.removeAttribute(\"data-src\")),e.dataset.srcset&&(e.setAttribute(\"srcset\",e.dataset.srcset),e.removeAttribute(\"data-srcset\"));const t=e.parentNode.querySelectorAll(\"source[data-srcset]\");for(let e of t)e.setAttribute(\"srcset\",e.dataset.srcset),e.removeAttribute(\"data-srcset\");e.complete&&(e.style.opacity=1,e.parentNode.parentNode.querySelector(\"[data-placeholder-image]\").style.opacity=0)}}</script></div><script type=\"application/json\" data-wp-inline-image-hydration=\"2\">{\"image\":{\"images\":{\"sources\":[],\"fallback\":{\"src\":\"/_gatsby/image/79a6a10d0413605c35bcb6d9ebf9e3e6/3fd703fd789c940ed30c9c507ff9d5dc/image-10.png?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwebguru.dev%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F04%2Fimage-10.png&a=w%3D256%26h%3D42%26fm%3Dpng%26q%3D90&cd=2023-04-13T03%3A57%3A54\",\"srcSet\":\"/_gatsby/image/79a6a10d0413605c35bcb6d9ebf9e3e6/3fd703fd789c940ed30c9c507ff9d5dc/image-10.png?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwebguru.dev%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F04%2Fimage-10.png&a=w%3D256%26h%3D42%26fm%3Dpng%26q%3D90&cd=2023-04-13T03%3A57%3A54 256w,/_gatsby/image/79a6a10d0413605c35bcb6d9ebf9e3e6/8b90fea6c5b5e215f87d6b6653e835f0/image-10.png?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwebguru.dev%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F04%2Fimage-10.png&a=w%3D512%26h%3D85%26fm%3Dpng%26q%3D90&cd=2023-04-13T03%3A57%3A54 512w,/_gatsby/image/79a6a10d0413605c35bcb6d9ebf9e3e6/5663903fab88f184af92ef37a377bd4c/image-10.png?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwebguru.dev%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F04%2Fimage-10.png&a=w%3D1024%26h%3D170%26fm%3Dpng%26q%3D90&cd=2023-04-13T03%3A57%3A54 1024w\",\"sizes\":\"(min-width: 1024px) 1024px, 100vw\"}},\"layout\":\"constrained\",\"width\":1024,\"height\":170},\"alt\":\"Steps to Implement Magnifier Widget in Magento 2 2\",\"className\":\"wp-image-1812 inline-gatsby-image-wrapper\",\"data-wp-inline-image\":\"2\"}</script></figure></div>\n\n\n<p></p>\n\n\n\n<p>4. Click on the &#8220;Create Theme&#8221; button.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>5. Enter a name for your new theme and click on the &#8220;Save&#8221; button.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Step 2: Create a New Module</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The next step is to create a new module. This can be done in the following steps:</p>\n\n\n\n<p>1. Log in to your server using SSH.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>2. Navigate to your Magento 2 installation directory.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>3. Run the following command to create a new module:</p>\n\n\n\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>lua\n\nphp bin/magento module:create --module-name=Namespace_ModuleName --vendor=Namespace --area=frontend</code></pre>\n\n\n\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Replace &#8220;Namespace_ModuleName&#8221; and &#8220;Namespace&#8221; with your desired module name and vendor name.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Step 3: Implement the Magnifier Widget</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The final step is to implement the magnifier widget. This can be done in the following steps:</p>\n\n\n\n<p>&nbsp;1. Create a new template file for your product view page. This can be done by creating a new file in the following directory:</p>\n\n\n\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>bash\n\napp/design/frontend/Namespace/Theme/Magento_Catalog/templates/product/view/gallery.phtml</code></pre>\n\n\n\n<p>2. Copy the contents of the default Magento 2 gallery.phtml file into your new template file.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>3. Add the following code to your new template file to implement the magnifier widget:</p>\n\n\n\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>php\n\n&lt;div data-role=\"magnifier\" data-magnifier-enabled=\"1\" data-magnifier-params='{\"width\": \"400\", \"height\": \"400\"}'&gt;\n\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;img class=\"gallery-placeholder\"\n\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;src=\"&lt;?php /* @escapeNotVerified */ echo $block-&gt;getImageBlock()-&gt;getImageUrl(); ?&gt;\"\n\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;data-src=\"&lt;?php /* @escapeNotVerified */ echo $block-&gt;getImageBlock()-&gt;getImageUrl(); ?&gt;\"\n\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;alt=\"&lt;?php /* @escapeNotVerified */ echo $block-&gt;escapeHtml($block-&gt;getProduct()-&gt;getName()) ?&gt;\"&gt;\n\n&lt;/div&gt;</code></pre>\n\n\n\n<p>This code creates a container for the magnifier widget, sets the width and height of the magnified image, and specifies the image source.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>4. Save your new template file and clear the Magento 2 cache by running the following command:</p>\n\n\n\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>python\n\nphp bin/magento cache:clean</code></pre>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Testing the Magnifier Widget:</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Before deploying the magnifier widget in your live store, it&#8217;s important to test it thoroughly to ensure that it works properly on different devices and browsers. You can use a testing tool such as BrowserStack or Sauce Labs to test the magnifier widget on various devices and operating systems. You can also test the widget on your own devices and ask your friends or colleagues to test it as well.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Customizing the Magnifier Widget:</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>You can customize the appearance and behavior of the magnifier widget by modifying the magnifier widget parameters. The available parameters include width, height, zoom level, animation speed, and more. You can also modify the CSS of the magnifier widget to change its appearance, such as the border color, background color, and position.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Using a Third-Party Extension:</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>If you&#8217;re not comfortable with coding, you can use a third-party extension to implement the magnifier widget in your Magento 2 store. There are many extensions available in the Magento Marketplace that offer different types of magnifier widgets with various features and customization options. You can choose an extension that best fits your needs and install it in your store.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Congratulations, you have successfully implemented a magnifier widget in Magento 2!</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Conclusion</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>In summary, adding a magnifier widget to your online store can improve the user experience by enabling customers to zoom in on product images. To implement the widget in Magento 2, you need to create a new theme, or module, or use a template file or programmatic approach. These steps can optimize your Magento 2 store for a more satisfying shopping experience for customers. The suitability of either approach depends on specific needs, and it&#8217;s critical to consider the advantages and disadvantages before choosing. <a href=\"/how-to-create-a-widget-programmatically-in-magento-2/\">Create the widget programmatically in Magento 2</a> that grants more control over its behavior, while using a template file may be more suitable for simpler use cases. Ultimately, the best approach depends on your store&#8217;s requirements and goals.</p>\n<div class='sfsi_Sicons sfsi_Sicons_position_left' style='float: none; vertical-align: middle; text-align:left'><div style='margin:0px 8px 0px 0px; line-height: 24px'><span>Please follow and like us:</span></div><div class='sfsi_socialwpr'><div class='sf_fb_share sf_icon' style='text-align:left;vertical-align: middle;'><a  target='_blank' rel='noopener' href='https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=/how-to-implement-magnifier-widget-in-magento-2/' style='display:inline-block;'><img class='sfsi_wicon'  data-pin-nopin='true' alt='fb-share-icon' title='Facebook Share' src='https://webguru.dev/wp-content/plugins/ultimate-social-media-icons/images/share_icons/fb_icons/en_US.svg' /></a></div><div class='sf_twiter sf_icon' style='display: inline-block;vertical-align: middle;width: auto;margin-left: 7px;'>\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<a target='_blank' rel='noopener' href='https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?text=How+to+Implement+Magnifier+Widget+in+Magento+2+https%3A%2F%2Fwebguru.dev%2Fhow-to-implement-magnifier-widget-in-magento-2%2F'style='display:inline-block' >\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<img data-pin-nopin= true class='sfsi_wicon' src='https://webguru.dev/wp-content/plugins/ultimate-social-media-icons/images/share_icons/Twitter_Tweet/en_US_Tweet.svg' alt='Tweet' title='Tweet' >\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</a>\r\n\t\t\t\t\t</div></div></div><div class=\"saboxplugin-wrap\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/Person\" itemscope itemprop=\"author\"><div class=\"saboxplugin-tab\"><div class=\"saboxplugin-gravatar\"><div data-gatsby-image-wrapper=\"\" style=\"position:relative;overflow:hidden;display:inline-block;vertical-align:top\" class=\"gatsby-image-wrapper gatsby-image-wrapper-constrained  inl